<b>Ingredients</b>
<br><div class="mobileAdPlacement"></div>
<ul><li> 1 Tbsp. mayonnaise </li><li> ½ avocado, coarsely chopped </li><li>Salt and pepper</li><li>1 6-inch whole-wheat pita pocket bread</li><li>2 slices cooked bacon</li><li>2-3 romaine or green leaf lettuce leaves</li><li>½ tomato, thinly sliced</li></ul><br>
<b>Preparation time:</b> 5 minutes<br>
<br>
<b>Steps:</b>
<br><div class="teadsAdPlacement"></div>
1. In a small bowl combine the mayonnaise and avocado and season with salt and pepper. <br>
2. Cut pita bread in half and open the pockets. Spoon some of the avocado spread into each pocket, then fill it with the bacon, lettuce, and tomato. Serve immediately.
